Show Description

From the Infowars web site :: On this Thursday, July 17 edition of The Alex Jones Show, Nightly News host David Knight hosts the first hour. David covers the news and features Alex's special report centered around a disturbing Guardian Centers video. Guardian Centers is an 830 acre "disaster preparedness and tactical training validation center" located in Georgia which is routinely used by FEMA and other government agencies to practice emergency response procedures. 

Alex covers Rex84 and other government and military exercises designed to facilitate martial law in America. 

On today's worldwide broadcast Alex talks with political documentary filmmaker Joel Gilbert about his latest film, There's No Place Like Utopia, a humorous and horrifying exploration of Progressivism, amnesty for illegals, race relations, Islam in America, political correctness, and Barack Obama. 

Alex also welcomes Dr. Peter Glidden (of Youngevity) back to the show. He is an advocate of wholistic health. His latest book is The MD Emperor Has No Clothes: Everybody Is Sick and I Know Why.
